results.name: Triangle read by rows where T(n,k) is the number of unlabeled simple connected graphs with n vertices and k bridges.
comment: A bridge is an edge that, if removed without removing any incident vertices, disconnects the graph. Unlabeled connected graphs with no bridges are counted by A007146 (unlabeled graphs with spanning edge-connectivity >= 2).
link: Gus Wiseman, Unlabeled connected graphs with 5 vertices and k bridges.
xref: Row sums without the k = 0 column are A052446.
Column k = 0 is A007146, if we assume A007146(0) = 1.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Aug 26 2019
